        1
        +
        
          tan
          
            2
          
        
        ⁡
        (
        x
        )
        .
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\frac {d}{dx}}\tan(x)=\sec ^{2}(x)={\frac {1}{\cos ^{2}(x)}}=1+\tan ^{2}(x).}
  
Inverse trigonometric functions:
  
    
      
        
          
